"title":"Cystitis",
"jsonContent":{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_id_s13",
"title":{
"__html":"Cystitis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"42f111",
"children":[
"Cystitis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_id_s13_1",
"title":{
"__html":"Prevention"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"c53b76",
"children":[
"Prevention"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"31becf",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"alert",
"children":[
"Screen for and treat asymptomatic bacteriuria only in patients who are pregnant or are about to undergo an invasive urologic procedure."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_id_s13_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Diagnosis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"523223",
"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"93b5ec",
"children":[
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"urinary tract infection",
"children":[
"UTI"
]
},
"s"
]
},
" (either cystitis or pyelonephritis) are classified as uncomplicated or complicated."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"9bbf5c",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Uncomplicated"
]
},
" UTI is acute cystitis and pyelonephritis occurring in healthy, nonpregnant women with no history of urinary tract abnormalities."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"807044",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Complicated"
]
},
" UTIs occur:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"b6d7d7",
"children":[
"in men and pregnant women"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"6390cc",
"children":[
"in the presence of foreign bodies (catheters, calculi)"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"1f284e",
"children":[
"in kidney disease"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"860f49",
"children":[
"in immunocompromised hosts"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"d5be33",
"children":[
"in obstruction and other causes of urinary retention"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"ecec70",
"children":[
"with recent antibiotic use"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"0c05f0",
"children":[
"Designating an infection as ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"complicated"
]
},
" influences the choice and duration of antimicrobial therapy and extent of investigation."
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"c0e971",
"children":[
"Age alone does not define a complicated versus uncomplicated infection."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_id_s13_3",
"title":{
"__html":"Testing"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"fa6a5a",
"children":[
"Testing"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"7ccae2",
"children":[
"Patients with uncomplicated cystitis do not require a urine culture but can be diagnosed with either:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"afc67a",
"children":[
"urine dipstick positive for leukocyte esterase and nitrites"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"81dabc",
"children":[
"≥10 ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"white blood cell",
"children":[
"WBC"
]
},
"s/μL and bacteriuria"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"da684d",
"children":[
"Obtain a urine culture for:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"90c333",
"children":[
"suspected pyelonephritis"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"9998bd",
"children":[
"complicated UTI"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"b9091a",
"children":[
"recurrent UTI"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"1093b3",
"children":[
"recent antibiotic treatment"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"c67cbe",
"children":[
"health care–associated UTI"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_id_s13_4",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"8e3eb9",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"For women with symptoms of uncomplicated cystitis"
]
},
", prescribing antibiotics over the telephone without seeing the patient or obtaining a urinalysis is acceptable."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"f138ff",
"children":[
"For empiric treatment of uncomplicated cystitis in ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"nonpregnant women"
]
},
", select one of the following:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"b95f2d",
"children":[
"3 days of oral trimethoprim-sulfamethoxazole"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"d67867",
"children":[
"5 days of oral nitrofurantoin"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"49f0de",
"children":[
"single dose of fosfomycin"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"01dc29",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"In patients at high risk for complicated UTI,"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"alert",
"children":[
"obtain a urine culture and initiate empiric treatment for 7 to 10 days with a fluoroquinolone."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"d707d2",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"For pregnant women,"
]
},
" choose 7 days of empiric therapy with amoxicillin-clavulanate, cefpodoxime, or cefixime. Obtain a urine culture after treatment."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"320f2f",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"For recurrent uncomplicated UTIs"
]
},
", select one or more of the following:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"7fe540",
"children":[
"postcoital antibiotic prophylaxis, particularly if UTIs are temporally associated with coitus"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"a8b695",
"children":[
"continuous antibiotic prophylaxis"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"fff1ec",
"children":[
"self-initiated therapy for frequent recurrent episodes"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"ba9a96",
"children":[
"Trimethoprim-sulfamethoxazole should not be used if it was taken in the preceding 3 months."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"2a6b11",
"children":[
"Do not schedule a routine follow-up urinalysis or culture after treatment for nonpregnant women with uncomplicated cystitis."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
}
]
},
